@arnuschky another thing here: there are several ways to provide authentication on the server side, each of them would lead to different security mechanisms. In case of default Django cookie-based authentication one need to use CSRF and your pull request is perfectly valuable. From another hand, if there is token-based authentication (OAUTH1/2), there are no cookies, including CSRF. If developer chooses to use this approach,  library should not force to use csrf (because it is simply redundant).

If you would like to contribute csrf mechanism, I would suggest to inherit  from `JSONRPCAPI` class and redefine `jsonrpc` method, something like this:

```python
class JSONRPCAPICSRF(JSONRPCAPI):
    def jsonrpc(self, request):
        return csrf_exempt(super(JSONRPCAPICSRF, self).jsonrpc)(self, request)
```

In this case current code still would work and new functionality would be implemented in a proper way.

