Hi @tlorens!

Now that I think about it, the main problem is that only the `jquery.tablesorter.combined.js` file is using a [UMD](https://github.com/umdjs/umd) wrapper. All the other js (in `extra`, `parsers` and `widgets` folder) files in the `dist` folder are wrapped in an [IIFE](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Glossary/IIFE).

I'll have to add a script to wrap all the js files in a UMD to fix this problem. Once that's done, you'll need to access the files using a path through `node_modules`. Something like this:

```js
var folder = './node_modules/tablesorter/dist/';

var tablesorterPager = require(folder + 'js/extras/jquery.tablesorter.pager.min.js');
var pathToCss = folder + 'css/jquery.tablesorter.pager.min.css';
```

