@andreif: I needed the same feature and wrote a patch for that, the branch is on my fork here: https://github.com/lindsay-stevens/xmltodict/tree/ordered-children-short-tags

It's got a flag to deal with mixed child ordering on parse and unparse. During parse it'll add an @\__order\__ attribute, on unparse it'll remove the attribute and sort the mixed nodes. Also has a bonus XHTML-ish feature to enable output of short-form of empty tags, e.g. "\<tag/\>" vs. "\<tag\>\</tag\>"

Not opened a PR for it yet since my previous one is still open and I didn't want to be annoying.

