Where you would use a template like:
```HTML+Django
{% load static %}

<div class="foo">
    <img src="{% static 'myapp/image/bar.png' %}">
    ....
</div>
```

If you didn't override LIBSASS_CUSTOM_FUNCTIONS, you can use the 'static' function in stylesheets:
```scss
.foo {
    background: url(static("myapp/image/bar.png"));
}
```
If your STATIC_URL is '/static/', this will be rendered as:
```css
.foo {
    background: url("/static/myapp/image/bar.png"));
}
```

Really, all the magic is done by Django and the libsass package (see the custom_functions parameter doc).

