@lgh2 That doesn't look like an error on the `setuptools` side, unless I'm reading the traceback wrong. Looks like the problem is when you call `f.read()`, you're failing to decode it.

I'm pretty sure the change you mentioned in the PKG-INFO writer would never have been hit by this anyway, but it's not clear what good it would do in this case anyway. The traceback you have still indicates pretty clearly where the problem was.

In fact, the [second change you mention](https://github.com/pypa/setuptools/pull/802/files#diff-81de4a30a55fcc3fb944f8387ea9ec94R1865) actually seems to make this *more lenient*. Now instead of just re-raising the error, the read will succeed (and write something with a bunch of error characters and/or [mojibake](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mojibake) in it, presumably) but warn the user rather than raising an error. This seems like a better behavior to me, since you probably don't want the whole operation blocked entirely just because someone sends some non-UTF-8 metadata.

