> Please fix it so that the activate script can be launched from a full path

This is really important.  *So* much code--not just the conda and conda-build code--uses full paths for reliability.  A lot of devops code for example.  Heck, I typically full-path both the `conda` and `activate` executables because I have so many different versions installed locally.  We'll need to figure out a solution here.

The more I think about this, the more I like the idea of *per-environment channel priorities*. For example, I have (at least) three types of environments: 
* ilastik environments, where we build many packages ourselves to make sure that everything fits together in the end user's (biologist's) installation;
* teaching environments, where I take everything from official channels to match the installations of my students;
* work environments, where I prioritize channels as needed, and where occasional problems are not critical as long as I know how to fix them.

All of them require different priorization. Moreover, I don't think that it is too complex to allow priority specification on a per-channel basis. In fact, I'm convinded that the priority mechanism can be designed such that it remains simple for normal users, but is highly customizable for power users -- I don't see a contradiction between these goals.

