Apologies about my lack of clarity concerning which part of your PR to move to wombat.
In wombat we have a function called `init_top_frame_notify` that contains an inner function `notify_top`. 
`notify_top` is used to send the `message.wb_type === "load"` to `ContentFrame` when `#replay_frame`'s `document.readystate === "complete"`.
I have embedded the location of this function below.
https://github.com/webrecorder/pywb/blob/2f062cf5c73097a19599b7f9c11dafe854d0f5c8/pywb/static/wombat.js#L3561-L3597

I believe if you do something like this in `notify_top`
```js
var icons = [];
var hicons = $wbwindow.document.querySelectorAll("link[rel*='icon']");
for (var i = 0; i < hicons.length; i++) {
    var hicon = hicons[i];
    icons.push({
         rel: hicon.rel,
         href: hicon.href
    })
}
var message = {
   "icons": icons,
   ....
}
``` 
And like so in `handle_message`
```js
if (type === 'load') {
    window.document.title = state.title + ' ' + state.ts;
    var head = document.querySelector('head');
    var len = state.icons.length;
    for (var i = 0; i < len; i++) {
        var icon = state.icons[i];
        var link = document.createElement('link');
        link.rel = icon.rel;
        link.href = icon.href;
        head.appendChild(link);
    }
}
```
We should be good to go :smiley:

